This diagram shows various string graphs.
Be sure to click on the toolbar's <icon>graph</icon> button to view them.

And now see the origin of the graph <icon>graph</icon> button.

By setting B, C, D to the underlying field for a category
of vector spaces one gets a different morphism from
the triple dual of A to itself than just the identity.
